HEADWORD: eastbound
<hw>eastbound</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>moving toward the
east; <as>as, <ex>eastbound</ex> trains</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eastward.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>designated for traffic moving toward the east; -- of
lanes in roads or railroads, or other traffic lanes; <as>as, the
<ex>eastbound</ex> lanes of Interstate 80 are blocked by an overturned
tractor-trailer; the train will leave on <ex>eastbound</ex> platform
5</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

